    "long_instructions": "A comic book enthusiast wants to create a visualization that shows a comparison of the number of wins each character has in a battle.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">BattleScene.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">isMatch()</code> method to return <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">true</code> if the main character and enemy character both match the given parameters. Otherwise return <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">false</code>.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">TheaterRunner.java</code>, choose two battles that match and pass them into the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">drawResults()</code> method.\r\n",
